Job Title: Manager - Business Partnering & Analysis | Growing Global Leader
Ad Text:
Ref: A000909

High-Impact Analysis
Key Stakeholder Leadership
Direct impact on projects

The Company

Robert Half Executive Search (RH ES) has been retained to appoint a commercially savvy and hands-on Manager - Business Partnering & Analysis with a well-respected, market leading manufacturing technology business.

With operations and solutions serving markets across Australia, New Zealand, and South East Asia, the business is renowned for its technical expertise, product quality, and commitment to innovation, design, manufacture, and distribution of highly engineered solutions.

The Role

Reporting to the Regional Finance Director, your focus will be on delivering financial insight, business analysis and decision support to support improved profitability, productivity and business improvement initiatives.

You will be the primary link between Finance and the broader business, working closely with Manufacturing, Operations, Sales, Marketing, to optimise business performance and ensure the business continues to apply best practice.

Key Responsibilities & Focus Areas

As the Manager - Business Partnering & Analysis, you will provide financial insight and technical expertise to guide decision-making, reporting directly to the Finance Director and acting as a critical resource to all ASEAN businesses.

High-Impact Analysis & Performance Management:
Analyse variances, trends, and KPIs to monitor financial and operational performance across the transactional landscape.
Develop and refine financial models to improve accuracy and insight.
Help drive accountability for performance across business units through clear reporting.
Strategic Finance & Decision Support:
Provide financial insight and modelling to support strategic choices and investment decisions.
Translate complex financial data into clear, actionable recommendations for senior leaders.
Expert Use of Excel & Financial Systems:
Utilise expert-level Excel skills to design and deliver innovative financial/commercial analysis, including budget management, forecasting, and on-demand planning.
Implement improvements to financial systems, models, and tools to increase efficiency and reliability.
Exceptional Stakeholder Engagement & Business Partnering:
Build strong relationships with operational and functional leaders, providing proactive financial guidance.
Act as a constructive challenger, supporting robust, data-driven decision-making.
Present complex insights clearly to non-financial stakeholders, tailoring communication to the audience. Your key stakeholders will include the Leadership Team and Business Unit/Operations Managers.
Leadership & Team Development:
Provide day-to-day leadership, guidance, and oversight to a team of primarily Management Accountants (direct reports).
Review and ensure accuracy, completeness, and quality of financial outputs.

What You Will Bring:

Tertiary Qualifications in Finance or Commerce disciplines.
CA/CPA or business qualification
Highly competent to lead, design, and deliver innovative financial/commercial analysis.
Demonstrated expertise in Excel is non-negotiable for complex modelling and analysis.
Expert skills in budget management control, forecasting, and on-demand planning.
Excellent analytical skills and attention to detail-you will proactively pick up errors and exceptions in reports.

Personal Qualities

Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills-the ability to influence and partner effectively across the business.
A resourceful, adaptable, and commercially minded approach.
Commitment to continuous improvement and service excellence.

This role offers the chance to make a tangible, immediate impact by strengthening financial discipline and delivering value within a significant, dynamic Australian enterprise.

Apply Today

Please send your resume by clicking on the apply button. Your application will be assessed within 3-5 working days. Please note only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

What's the role?

Are you a social media and off-platform leader looking for a role with scale, influence, and real impact? This oneʼs for you.

Australians are spending more time than ever on a diversifying network of platforms, and increasingly turning to them for news. The challenge for publishers is clear: meet audiences where they are and deliver value in ways that strengthen the future of journalism.

This new role is critical to that mission. Partnering with the Head of Platform Content Strategy, youʼll be leading the delivery of News Corpʼs enterprise off-platform strategy, including social media, Apple News, AI, and emerging platforms.
Spanning implementation, measurement, governance, tools, experimentation, and capability building, youʼll also lead, coach, and support our many mastheads and brands to deliver exceptional outcomes off-platform.

In short, youʼll be one of the key drivers ensuring we maximise the value of our content off-platform, to help our journalism serve more Australians, more often.

What You'll Do

Initiative Leadership & Project Management
● Lead the end-to-end delivery of News Corp Australiaʼs off-platform strategy projects.
● Partner with the Head of Platform Content Strategy to manage the ongoing development and evolution of the off-platform strategy and roadmap, aligning initiatives with broader business objectives and audience growth goals.
● Guide and coach brands to implement the enterprise off-platform strategy through tailored playbooks and frameworks that drive excellence across channels.
● Lead enterprise insights and reporting, translating performance data into clear, actionable narratives that inform strategic direction and demonstrate impact.
● Manage strong partnerships with major platforms and vendors, ensuring News Corpʼs strategic priorities and commercial interests are consistently represented.

Consultation & Capability
● Design and lead consultation, workshops, learning initiatives, and forums that strengthen off-platform performance and capability.
● Build and nurture a connected community of practice across the business to drive collaboration, share emerging insights, and scale best practices.
● Partner with brands and mastheads on high-impact campaigns and editorial initiatives, providing strategic guidance on audience growth, engagement, and monetisation.
● Collaborate with cross-functional partners across News Corp to align efforts, share intelligence, and embed consistent off-platform excellence.

Emerging Platforms & Innovation
● Lead initiatives to evaluate, pilot, and scale emerging off-platform technologies, formats, and content opportunities.
● Partner with our teams to identify and test new pathways for audience growth and monetisation
● Identify and interpret shifts in algorithms, distribution models, and platform capabilities to inform strategic direction.
● Capture learnings from experimentation and translate them into frameworks, playbooks, and case studies that embed innovation across the organisation.

Who are you?

Youʼre a senior leader who moves confidently in a fast-changing landscape, learns quickly, and brings clarity to complexity. You can influence at all levels, collaborate with teams across a large organisation and guide outcomes on the platforms that matter.

● 8+ experience in social media, strategy, audience development, or related fields.
● Proven experience leading large-scale, cross-functional projects or programs within complex, multi-brand organisations.
● Demonstrated understanding of social, search, video, and aggregator ecosystems, including platform governance and monetisation models.
● Strong capability in stakeholder management, change leadership, and data-informed decision-making.
● Experience engaging with technology vendors and platform partners to drive business outcomes.
● Naturally analytical thinker who can interrogate data to distill insights, and recommend
● Tertiary qualification in media, communications, marketing, business, or a related discipline is desirable

News Benefits

News Benefits is our way of saying thank you to our people for their valued contribution to News, our audiences, clients and communities. Thanking them for the great things they do daily, for the greater good of Australia. Our benefits include:

Exclusively ours - Access to publications and products from across the News Corp family

Health & wellbeing - Advice, support and facilities for healthy minds and bodies (including an onsite gym at our Adelaide, Brisbane & Sydney offices) 

Time off - News offers a range of leave options to support your personal needs and moments that matter in life: Parental leave, Birthday leave, Volunteer leave, Career break and Compassionate leave.

Helping you grow - Development opportunities (including diversity and inclusion - focused education series) and recognition

Financial wellbeing - Support on making the most of your money

Perks & discounts - Exclusive offers across a range of products and services

Giving back - Make a difference to our communities.

Workplace Inclusion and facilities – Engage with your passions through various employee-resource groups and accessibility to multi-faith quiet rooms & parents’ rooms

Who are we?

We are proud to be Australia’s most impactful media group, we’re even prouder of what we stand for. Together, we inform, advocate and inspire all Australians, for a better Australia.

With over 150 brands across news, sport and lifestyle, News Corp Australia is trusted by over 18 million Australians a month to provide the information and inspiration they seek.

Renowned for world-class journalism and marketing services nationally and internationally, we offer a fast-paced environment that encourages individuals to take control of their future and challenge themselves in ever-changing fields.

What’s next?

Grant Thornton Australia is one of the world's leading independently-owned and managed accounting, advisory and consulting firms.

About this role

Join our innovative Digital Team as a Senior Data Analyst and embark on a journey where your skills in data modelling, integration and analysis will be pivotal in shaping our business landscape. This permanent, full-time position sits within our Applications, Data and Integration team, and offers the unique opportunity to collaborate with a close-knit team of experts, including Data Scientists, BI Specialists and Application Specialists. Building on our greenfield data environment, your contributions will leave a lasting impact as you implement data models and pipelines that support meaningful and actionable analytics, helping to drive positive change with an engaged and supportive business.  

Key responsibilities

Partner with stakeholders across the business to gather data and reporting requirements, and translate them into effective, scalable analytics solutions. 

Build and maintain clean, reliable datasets using SQL and Python within Databricks, supporting both operational reporting and strategic analysis. 

Develop and deliver insightful dashboards and reports using Power BI to help drive data-informed decisions. 

Use Python/pySpark in Databricks to automate data preparation, analysis, and reporting workflows. 

Support the development and improvement of data pipelines and processes in collaboration with other data specialists, ensuring data is accurate, timely, and accessible. 

Work with cloud-based data platforms, particularly within Microsoft Azure. Collaborate with engineering team members to ensure data solutions are secure, reliable, and well-integrated. 

Skills & experience

Advanced SQL skills for querying and transforming large datasets across various sources. 

Proficiency in Python/pySpark, particularly in the context of Databricks, for data manipulation, analysis, and automation. 

Hands-on experience working in Databricks, including familiarity with notebooks, workflows, and collaborative data development. 

Strong experience building dashboards and data models in Power BI or similar BI tools. 

Comfortable working with cloud-based data platforms, ideally within Azure. 

Ability to collaborate with both technical teams and non-technical stakeholders to deliver data solutions that meet business needs. 

Familiarity with data best practices, including governance, quality, and documentation. 

If you’re interested in this role but don’t feel that you match every single one of our requirements, we would still love to hear from you and explore the unique skillset and attributes that you can bring to the team. 

Reach your remarkable

At Grant Thornton we do things differently because we understand that when you strive for better and care about what you do remarkable things are possible. We’re a dynamic and authentic mix of backgrounds, perspectives and ways of thinking. We’re driven by our shared purpose – we care for our people, clients and communities and support them to thrive.

With us, you’ll be exposed to challenging and rewarding opportunities – building your confidence and capabilities at every step. You’ll be supported, motivated and inspired by a team of passionate and caring collaborators and leaders. You’ll be empowered to build a career path that’s tailored to you and encouraged to make a meaningful difference. And we’ll make sure the excellence you deliver and the impact you make is always seen, felt and celebrated.

9-day fortnight with no salary reduction

And many more!

Join Kinetic IT as a Lead Security Analyst on a 12 month Fixed Term Contract, working on site with one of our largest Perth-based clients 

In this role, you’ll play a key part in shaping the maturity of our cyber defence capability, partnering closely with the Security Operations Manager to uplift detection, response, and threat intelligence functions. You’ll provide hands-on technical leadership to the L1 and L2 analysts, guide complex investigations, and lead improvements across the SOC’s processes, tools, and overall security posture.

This is an opportunity to influence direction, drive capability uplift, and help safeguard a high-profile environment through proactive threat hunting and coordinated incident response.

Responsibilities will include:

Leading day-to-day technical operations of the SOC, guiding L1/L2 analysts and owning escalation paths.
Acting as as the Sentinel subject-matter expert: rule tuning, analytic creation, workbook/dashboards, data connector configuration, and automation via Logic Apps.
Owning threat-hunting operations using KQL, intelligence feeds, and Sentinel's hunting tools to identify unknown or emerging threats
Ensuring incident documentation, evidence handling, and reporting to meet governance, privacy, and audit expectations.
Providing technical mentorship, upskilling, and coaching to the analyst team, ensuring consistent analytical quality.
Managing integrations between Sentinel and Tenable, Defender stack, and SNOW, validating data flows and resolving ingestion issues.
Driving continuous improvement of playbooks, response procedures, and SOC workflows aligned to ISM, Essential 8, and DOE requirements.
Serving as the technical liaison with DOE stakeholders, providing clear briefings, incident summaries, and recommendations for security uplift.

What you’ll bring to the table:

Prior experience leading SOC operations and guiding L1/L2 analysts through escalations and complex investigations.
Deep expertise with Microsoft Sentinel, including rule tuning, analytics, hunting, dashboards, data connectors, and Logic Apps automation.
Proven capability in high-severity incident response, including triage, investigation, containment, and clear documentation.
Advanced detection engineering and threat-hunting skills using KQL, intelligence feeds, and behavioural analytics.
Experience managing integrations across Sentinel, Defender, Tenable, and ServiceNow.
Ability to uplift team capability through mentorship, coaching, and consistent analytical standards.
Strong communication skills with the confidence to brief stakeholders and provide security uplift recommendations.

We are seeking a highly skilled SAS solution designer to drive the successful delivery of technical solutions. The ideal candidate will be responsible for handling business requirements, impact analysis, effort estimation, solution design, governance activities, and technical documentation.



Key Responsibilities:
Collaborate with Credit Risk Business Stakeholders, Service Owners, Solution Engineers, and Line of Business (LOB) Leads to prioritize, size, and assess requirements and backlog.
Work closely with business units to understand Credit Risk-related data elements, including reference data, metadata, and data lineage.
Guide Agile teams in designing, developing, testing, implementing, and supporting technical solutions using full-stack development tools, technologies, and DevOps processes.
Translate business requirements into IT solution concepts and designs.
Develop solution architectures that ensure successful implementation while aligning with design principles and standards.
Conduct root cause analysis for production incidents, identify design defects or requirement gaps, and provide effective solutions.
Provide third-line support for technical issues where necessary.
Contribute to high-level IT & Business Solution Design documents.
Advise the business on the effective application of technologies.
Support end-to-end implementation planning.
Oversee and validate proposed complex changes to business services to ensure ongoing stability and sustainability.
Deliver cost estimates for design and development phases in collaboration with architects, business analysts, project managers, subject matter experts, and solution providers.
Assist Solution Engineers and Data Engineers in design and development.
Contribute to strategic design, development, and deployment supporting projects and deliverables.
Required Professional and Technical Expertise:
3+ years of experience as a SAS Tech Lead / Senior Developer in a similar role.
5+ years of experience in projects or delivering business and technology solutions involving complex data engineering processes.
5+ years of Advanced SQL and SAS experience, particularly in data manipulation and cleansing using Base SAS, SAS/Macro, SAS DI Studio, SAS Enterprise Guide, SAS Management Console, and overall SAS Platform.
Experience in Big Data technologies (Hadoop, Spark, Hive, HBase, Python) is a plus.
Experience in API Development (Java Spring, MVC) and Azure Cloud (Synapse Analytics, CosmosDB) is advantageous.
Knowledge of data warehousing, modeling, and integration tools such as Informatica, Sterling, and business intelligence tools like Power BI, Tableau.
Experience designing solutions within SAS 9.4 or Viya platform.
Hands-on experience in Azure cloud environments.

About the Role
Capstone are partnering with an organisation currently expanding their team by hiring a Portfolio Benefits Analyst. They are seeking someone highly analytical with strong communication skills to work across the enterprise to track, report, and ensure that portfolio benefits and investment outcomes are realised. This is a 12-month Fixed Term Contract initially, with the scope to move into a permanent role at the conclusion of this period. 

Key Responsibilities:
Take ownership of the Benefits Register and analyse project benefits performance, ensuring any risks, trends, and variances are tracked and reported. 
Support the development of post-project implementation reviews (PIRs) by qualifying realised outcomes and quantifying benefits. 
Create regular and ad-hoc benefits reports to be presented at enterprise meetings such as SteerCo's, InvestmentCo's, and ExCo's. 
Contribute to the development of frameworks, tools, and the integration of benefits information into planning/prioritisation processes.
Key Requirements:
Demonstrable hands-on experience in analysing and managing the benefits realisation for an enterprise portfolio/project management office. Similarly held roles include EPMO Analyst, PMO Analyst, Project Portfolio Analyst etc. 
Top-tier analytical skills in data interpretation, dashboard creation (using Excel or PowerBI), and portfolio performance analysis in the context of end-to-end project delivery. 
Prior experience in capital-heavy industries like utilities, aviation, or infrastructure is very highly regarded. 

If you are interested in this opportunity please either apply directly OR reach out to robert@capstonerecruitment.com.au

As the National Manager - Finance Business Partner based in Canberra, you will be responsible for guiding the organisation's financial planning, budgeting, forecasting, and performance analysis.

You will provide expert financial insights to senior leaders, ensuring alignment between financial outcomes and organisational priorities, while driving strong governance and supporting informed, data-driven decision-making across the business.

Details about the Client

ADF Careers is the largest workforce outsourcing solution in the southern hemisphere with over 80,000 applications received on average each year.
ADF Careers is on a mission to recruit the right people, in the right numbers, at the right time to support the Australian Defence Force to build, sustain and maximise Defence capability.


Our people are our greatest asset. We recognise and respect our people's need to work in ways that support their careers, families, and lifestyle. That's why we offer flexible working arrangements, learning pathways, additional leave entitlements and extensive corporate discounts across a variety of product and services. We want our people to be financially rewarded; to feel good and to go beyond what they thought possible at work.

Be you, and we'll be better together.

To find out more about our great employee benefits and what it's like to be part of the team, reach out to our friendly talent acquisition team.

Job Description

The National Manager - Finance Business Partner is a strategic leadership role responsible for leading the organisation's financial planning, budgeting, forecasting, pricing and performance analysis team. This role works closely with senior leaders and provides strategic insight and analytical leadership to inform decision-making strengthen financial governance and drive business performance. Based at our Headquarters in Canberra, this role is the first point of contact for all Finance Business Partner matters, providing expert advice to our Senior Leadership Team and supporting the Head of Finance to ensure alignment between financial outcomes and organisational priorities.

You will:

Partner with business leaders and support the development of annual budgets, rolling forecasts and scenario modelling aligned with business plans
Partner with Head of Functions and National Managers to interpret financial results and translate into actional insights for operational and strategic improvement
Provide strategic financial advice to the DFR Executive Leadership team and senior stakeholder
Identify financial levers, risks, opportunities and emerging trends to inform organisational strategy and priorities
Liaise directly with Commonwealth representatives with regards to financial queries and requests relating to DFR
Develop and maintain pricing models and strategies to ensure competitive positioning, profitability and compliance with Adecco DFR objectives.
Oversee monthly management reporting, variance analysis and executive-level committee financial insights and ensure integrity and timeliness of all reporting to internal and external stakeholders
Partner with the Finance Leadership Team to provide aligned, consistent and effective people capability services for Adecco DFR
Continuously improve Finance Business Partnering processes and offerings to support the Adecco DFR organisation.
Lead and develop a high performing team of Financial Analysts to deliver high-quality analysis, advice and service
Build financial literacy and accountability across DFR functions
Act as deputy to the Head of Finance, representing the finance function in internal and external forums as required
Maintain industry knowledge and appropriate accreditation to ensure exceptional level of support to the business.
Develop, manage and maintain a high service level client relationship through the provision of services that meet or exceed the expectations of Defence and the DFR Adecco contract, further encouraging a strong and ongoing relationship between Adecco and the Commonwealth of Australia.

Candidate's Profile

If you have worked in a similar position or just looking for your next opportunity that will make an impact, we want to speak with you.

Your background will demonstrate:

Extensive experience leading FP&A and/or finance business partnering functions in a complex or large-scale organisations
Demonstrated ability to provide strategic financial leadership and influence senior stakeholders
Strong people leadership and coaching capability
Significant analytical skillset, including the utilisation of BI and reporting tools
High-level communication, influencing, and stakeholder engagement skills.
Resilient and adaptable mindset, with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced and everchanging environment.
Experience with enterprise-level financial systems and performance reporting tools e.g Microsoft Dynamics 365, PowerBI

To apply for this position, you must be an Australian citizen and have the ability to maintain an Australian AGSVA security clearance.

How to apply

If eligible, please submit your resume; applications are open to all qualified Australian citizens regardless of their background, identity, experiences and beliefs.

If you need assistance during our recruitment process, please email Victoria Emms at victoria.emms@adecco.com.au for a confidential conversation.

To apply for this position, please submit your application online through our designated platform. The deadline for applications is 11:30 PM (AEST) on Friday 19th December. It's important to note that applications will be reviewed and processed as they are received.

Job Title: General Manager - Client success & Research Transformation
Ad Text:
Endpoint IQ is a Brisbane-based SaaS company working with universities, research institutes, and health services across Australia, New Zealand, and overseas. Our platforms streamline the end‑to‑end research management pipeline, so researchers spend less time on admin and more time on impact.

We’re looking for a solutions‑focused, personable leader for our Client Success and Implementation team. We’re a medium‑sized, specialist team with low ego, a collaborative style, and close relationships with our clients. With the pace of change across higher education, this role is ideal for someone who wants to help shape the next generation of research management systems while staying connected to the sector.

You will:

Lead a multidisciplinary team of project managers and product specialists (~12FTE) delivering multiple concurrent implementations (10–24 month programmes)

Bring research management expertise to challenge "lift and shift" processes and design better ways of working for our clients

Own our implementation framework and delivery standards across institutions in Australia and overseas

Ensure Level 2 application support and product-specialist knowledge flow cleanly through to our developers and support engineers

Support Sales with research-literate input to proposals and take part in pre-sales demos for new and upsell opportunities.

About you

You understand the research management ecosystem and how universities and health services actually get work done. You may have come up through a Research Office, Ethics and Governance, Grants, or Graduate Research, or you may have led delivery or support for research‑adjacent software. What matters most is practical experience helping researchers and professional staff navigate processes such as ethics review, grants and contracts, HDR candidature, or post‑award finance, and turning that understanding into reliable delivery, clear communication, and measurable outcomes.

You’ve worked across multiple stakeholder groups and are comfortable balancing day‑to‑day matters with the dynamics of multiple streams of project delivery. Whether your path has been operational within a research intensive organisation or product/delivery for a vendor you will bring credibility with research management professionals and the judgement to lead a team that’s close to clients and outcomes.

What you’ll bring

Meaningful experience in research management or a closely related domain, with fluency in processes like ethics/governance, grants and contracts, HDR/GR, or post‑award.

A track record delivering or supporting business systems, ideally SaaS.

Strength in stakeholder engagement across academic, professional, and IT groups, with clear, plain‑language communication.

Comfort moving between detail and big picture: from root‑cause analysis and SOPs to roadmap, prioritisation, and acceptance.

Team leadership that’s low‑ego, collaborative, and oriented to service quality and measurable client outcomes.

Why join Endpoint IQ

Together building prosperity in the Kimberley and beyond — Safety, Sustainability, Community: it’s in our DNA.
 
At KMS, success is not just what we do — it’s how we do it. We’re seeking a hands on, outcomes focused Principal Continuous Improvement to embed a culture of improvement and lift performance across the business. You’ll be a trusted advisor to senior leaders and own enterprise level programs that strengthen governance, sustainability and stakeholder confidence.
 
About the Project

Kimberley Mineral Sands Pty Ltd (KMS) is a 50/50 joint venture between Sheffield Resources Limited and YGH Australia Investment Pty Ltd (Yansteel). The Thunderbird Mineral Sands Operation (Thunderbird) is located mid-way between Derby and Broome, in the Kimberley region of Western Australia. 

Thunderbird is one of the largest and highest-grade zircon mineral sands deposits in the world and contains valuable heavy minerals including ilmenite, zircon, leucoxene, and rutile, which are extracted and exported via the Port of Broome. 

Our head office is based in Broome, and together we are focused on delivering economic and social benefits for the West Kimberley and its communities. We do this through living our values of Integrity, Accountability, Humility, Co-Creation and Inclusivity. 



About the Role

Location: Perth or Broome (Monday–Friday corporate roster) with regular travel to the Thunderbird site
Department: Commercial & Finance
Reports to: Head of Commercial
 

What you’ll lead

Enterprise Continuous Improvement (CI) framework: design, implement and monitor a practical improvement framework aligned to organisational strategy; track outcomes and benefits with clear reporting.
Stewardship (organisational “wiring”) Program: own the design, governance and activities cadence (balanced scorecards, dashboards, KPIs) to drive accountability, transparency and responsible resource management.
Priority improvement delivery: identify and prioritise opportunities; facilitate CI activities such as value stream mapping, problem solving and idea generation; lead compliant process enhancements and sustainment plans.
Culture & capability: coach and mentor leaders and teams in CI methods (Lean, Six Sigma); develop tools, templates and training that build capability.
HS&E and risk alignment: ensure initiatives align with policies, risk frameworks, compliance requirements and our zero harm expectations.


About You
Degree in Business, Management or related discipline.
8+ years’ experience in continuous improvement, process optimisation or organisational development in complex environments.
Certification in Lean/Six Sigma or equivalent experience.
Strong analytics with the ability to translate data into actionable insights.
Highly effective stakeholder engagement and communication; you build trust quickly and collaborate to deliver meaningful change.
Leadership qualities that fit our environment: resilience and adaptability, a practical problem solving mindset, persistence and strong emotional intelligence.

Why join KMS?

Impact at enterprise scale: shape systems that improve performance and stewardship across the business.
Exposure & trust: partner closely with senior leaders; your advice and delivery will be visible and valued.
Community & purpose: contribute to prosperity in the Kimberley and beyond, grounded in safety and sustainability

Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion

KMS is committed to advancing an inclusive and diverse workforce culture and environment where people feel comfortable to be themselves. We acknowledge the different skills, experiences, and perspectives that people from diverse backgrounds including, race, ethnicity, disability, age, gender identity and sexual orientation bring to the workplace, will only strengthen our workforce.

We strongly encourage applications from our key priority communities – Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, women, youth, and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.  

How to Apply

Please submit your application via seek, or the KMS Careers Portal. If you have questions, contact Recruitment at recruitment@kmsands.com.au. Applications are reviewed as they are received and the advert may be removed should we find a suitable applicant.
